,Recommended,253770,19750855,"Posted: 17 December, 2015",all,DeanGeddes,"Firstly, I'd like to start by saying that this is a game of average quality. I would still recommed it to someone looking for a bus simualator game, mostly due to it's cheap price. It has its pros and cons though, which I am going to metion here.Here are some of the pros:- You can freely drive your bus around the city.- The interior design of the bus is quite nice.- Lots of camera views, especially in the driver's seat.- All of the switches, buttons, and levers in the cab do something, (no dummy buttons).- Lots of routes to drive around the city.- You can walk around (free movement).- Controller support.However, the cons include:- Only one game mode.- They make you remember a password at the start of the first ever game that you then have to put in to make the cash register work every time at the start of each game!- Cash register very complicated to work and there is also no tutorial.- The bus announcements are in German only, despite it saying on the Steam Store page that the game includes 'Full Audio' in English.- If you crash into another vehicle, you have to wait 30 seconds before it becomes invisible and you can drive on.- It is impossible to drive around tight bends without hitting a vehicle on the inside.There are also faults with the game, for example:- Quite often someone rings the bell to get off, but when you open the back and front doors at the next bus stop, no-one gets off.- When driving towards a bus stop, you cannot tell if some of the pedestrians are walking to the bus stop to get on your bus, or are just going to walk straight past, because their heads only look forwards.- The cash register sometimes just stops working and you cannot press any keys.- It is not very realistic because the stop bell always gets rung at exactly the same number of seconds after driving past or leaving the previous bus stop. In real life, it could be rung at any time between stops.Overall, this is an average game. Although I'd recommend it, I would say go for Munich Bus Simulator (also available on Steam). It has none of the faults that I previously mentioned. It is more expensive but it is newer and so much better. You get what you pay for. This is a cheap game so I can't complain about value."
